Rating: 3
I really enjoyed this. It was flavorful and fresh-tasting. I liked the kalamata olives and the topping of feta, which really made it work. A couple things I did that you might consider... I added some cayenne pepper for a kick, some fresh cilantro at the very end, some grated orange peel during cooking (as another cook suggested) and I went easy on the orange segments themselves (I was afraid too many would make it too sweet). I don't consider these major changes. It was fast, healthy and delicious.

Rating: 3
I have been messing around with this recipe quite a bit. Here is what I do now: I use tailpia instead of halibut, 1 chopped fresh organge, 2 plum tomatoes diced, 1/2 c. fresh OJ, 1/4 c. minced shallot, 3 T fresh lemon juice, 2 1/2 T olive oil, 1/4 c. minced kalmata olives, 2 T capers, 2 t rosemary. I also use cajun seasoning and sprigs of rosemary on the tailapia in addition to the orange pieces. Very refreshing dish!

