Rating: 4
This was wonderful. The flavors blended wonderfully. I made a couple of changes, out of necessity and I am looking forward to trying the recipe again, as is. I couldn't get good Halibut, so I used Sea Bass. I quartered fresh grape tomatoes rather than using canned ones. The feta cheese with the sea bass was a wonderful combination, and the orange juice added another level of taste that was out of this world. Definitely a keeper. With the sea bass, you can cut the steaming time to 9 or 10 min. I served it with wilted spinicn with bacon, and that worked very nicely, also.